Part A – SNS: Create topic and send to email
AWS Console → search SNS → Topics → Create topic.
Type: Standard, Name: MyEmailTopic → Create topic.
Open topic → Subscriptions tab → Create subscription.
Protocol: Email, Endpoint: your email address → Create.
Check inbox → click Confirm subscription link.
Back in SNS → open topic → click Publish message.
Subject: Test Mail, Body: Hello this is SNS test → Publish message.
Verify email is received.
Part B – S3 Upload → SNS → Email
Create S3 bucket: my-upload-bucket-2026 (same region as SNS).
Reuse or create SNS topic: S3UploadNotification (confirm email subscription).
Open SNS Topic → Access policy → Edit. Add policy (replace ARNs & account ID):
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Id": "S3EventNotificationPolicy",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "AllowS3ToPublish",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {
        "Service": "s3.amazonaws.com"
      },
      "Action": "SNS:Publish",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:sns:us-east-1:447640317537:s3-event-topic",
      "Condition": {
        "ArnLike": {
          "aws:SourceArn": "arn:aws:s3:::your-bucket-name"
        },
        "StringEquals": {
          "aws:SourceAccount": "447640317537"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}
Open S3 bucket → Properties → Event notifications → Create event notification.
Name: UploadNotification, Event type: All object create events, Destination: SNS → choose your topic → Save.
Upload any file to S3 → verify email notification arrives.
Part C – SQS: Create queue and send/receive message
AWS Console → search SQS → Create queue.
Type: Standard, Name: MyQueue → Create queue.
Open MyQueue → Send and receive messages.
Message body: Hello this is SQS test message → Send message.
Click Poll for messages → message appears.
(Optional) Select message → Delete message.
Part D – Full pipeline: S3 → SNS → SQS → Lambda
S3: Create bucket mys3eventbucket123.
SNS: Create topic MyS3SNSTopic → copy Topic ARN.
SQS: Create queue MyS3Queue → copy Queue ARN.
Subscribe SQS to SNS: Open topic → Create subscription → Protocol: Amazon SQS, Endpoint: MyS3Queue → Create.
SQS Access Policy: Open MyS3Queue → Access Policy → Edit → add policy:
{
  "Statement": [{
    "Effect": "Allow",
    "Principal": {"Service": "sns.amazonaws.com"},
    "Action": "sqs:SendMessage",
    "Resource": "SQS_ARN",
    "Condition": {"ArnEquals": {"aws:SourceArn": "SNS_ARN"}}
  }]
}
SNS Access Policy: Open SNS Topic → Edit access policy (same as Part B policy above with S3/account values).
S3 Event Notification: Bucket → Properties → Event notifications → Create: name S3UploadEvent, All object create events, Destination: SNS → MyS3SNSTopic → Save.
Upload a test file to S3 → open SQS → Send and receive messages → Poll for messages → verify message appears.
Lambda Consumer: Create function SQSConsumerFunction, Runtime: Python 3.x.
Add trigger → SQS → choose MyS3Queue → Add.
Replace function code:
def lambda_handler(event, context):
    for record in event['Records']:
        print("Message received from SQS:")
        print(record['body'])
    return {
        'statusCode': 200,
        'body': 'Message processed successfully'
    }
Click Deploy. Upload another file to S3 → check Lambda logs to verify processing.
